The type or area of uncertainty. (eg. origin, preference, valuation) 

Code Type value = HEADARSTYP

Property.name: AqisConcernCode
Property.description: The type of AQIS concern that has been nominated for the Declaration.

Property.name: AmountTypeInstanceId
Property.description: The code used to refer to the type of monetary amount.

Property.name: AustralianDollarAmount
Property.description: The value that is the Australian dollar monetary amount.

Property.name: ExchangeRateValue
Property.description: The exchange rate as retrieved which was used to calculate the Australian Dollar Amount.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the line.

Property.name: AirlineCode
Property.description: The IATA code that identifies the airline carrying the cargo.

Property.name: ArrivalDate
Property.description: The date the ship or aircraft carrying the cargo arrived or is expected to arrive at the port where the cargo is to be unloaded. For parcels post cargo it is the date that the parcels post card was issued.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the snapshot is the current snapshot for the cargo header.

Property.name: CustomsReceiptNumber
Property.description: The number that identifies the Customs Reciept (eg B390) issued when goods have been detained by Customs pending action by Customs or the importer.

Property.name: DeliveryClientInstanceId
Property.description: The client instance id for the referenced client to whom the shipment/ goods are finally destined.

Property.name: DischargePortCode
Property.description: The UNLOCODE for the Australian port, airport or parcels post centre at which the goods were unloaded.

Property.name: FirstArrivalDate
Property.description: The date that the ship or aircraft carrying the cargo arrived or is expected to arrive, at the first Australian port at which it will discharge cargo. A ship or aircraft may visit, and discharge cargo at a number of ports during a flight or voyage. This is not required for parcels post cargo.

Property.name: FirstArrivalPortCode
Property.description: The UNLOCODE for the first Australian port that the ship or aircraft carrying the cargo is expected to discharge cargo. A ship or aircraft may visit, and discharge cargo at a number of ports during a flight or voyage. This is not required for parcels post cargo.

Property.name: GrossWeight
Property.description: The total gross weight of the cargo included in the declaration.  It includes the packing but excludes the carrier's equipment.

Property.name: GrossWeightUnit
Property.description: The unit of weight in which the gross weight is expressed.  Must be a unit that is convertible to kilograms.

Property.name: LinkingVoygNum
Property.description: This attribute is used for linking the import declaration to the cargo report.  By removing characters based on a set of rules this attribute will match the voyage number on the cargo report

Property.name: LoadingPortCode
Property.description: The UNLOCODE for the overseas port at which the cargo was loaded onto the ship or aircraft. It is optional for parcels post cargo.

Property.name: MarksAndNumberDescription
Property.description: A free text field describing the package marks and numbers for all packages associated with the Import Declaration and any other identifying marks and brands on the packages being imported.  Marks descriptions are usually listed on the packing list and Bill of Lading or Air Waybill.

Property.name: PackageCount
Property.description: The number of packages contained in the Transport Header of a FID with a transport type of 'Other'. These FIDs do not have transport lines, so the package count is stored at the Transport Header level.

Property.name: VesselIdentifier
Property.description: The number assigned to the vessel by a registration authority.  The most commonly used registration authority is Lloyds of London.

Property.name: VoyageNumber
Property.description: The number assigned by the Principal Agent for a voyage.

Property.name: CargoType
Property.description:
Identifies whether the cargo is containerised, non-containerised, combination, bulk etc. See Cargo Type code list.  

This attribute is only populated for declarations where the mode of transport is sea.

Property.name: ContainerNumber
Property.description: The number that identifies the container in which the goods for the line of cargo are carried. This attribute is only populated for declarations where the mode of transport is sea.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the snapshot is the current snapshot for the cargo line.

Property.name: HouseAirWaybillId
Property.description: For air cargo, where the transportation of the goods is arranged by a cargo handler rather than directly by the airline company, this is number of the house air waybill issued by the cargo handler for the transportation of the goods. The house air waybill number is used in conjunction with the master air waybill number to uniquely identify the house air waybill.

Property.name: HouseBillOfLadingNumber
Property.description: For sea cargo, where the transportation of the goods is arranged by a cargo handler rather than directly by the shipping company, this is number of the house bill of lading issued by the cargo handler for the transportation of the goods. The house bill of lading number is used in conjunction with the ocean bill of lading number to uniquely identify the house bill of lading.

Property.name: LineActionCode
Property.description: Shows whether the line has been inserted, changed or deleted.

Property.name: LinkedBillLineTimestamp
Property.description: Where the Linking Master Bill Of Ladg Num is populated, and a matching Sea Bill has been found, the Linked Bill Line Timestamp will hold the Creation Timestamp of the Sea Bill Line to which the Ocean Bill Of Lading Number and House Bill of Lading Number have been matched.

Property.name: LinkedBillTimestamp
Property.description:
Where the Linking Master Air Waybill Num is populated, and a matching air Bill has been found, the Linked Bill Timestamp will hold the Effective Timestamp of the matching Bill.
Where the Linking Master Bill Of Ladg Num is populated, and a matching Sea Bill has been found, the Linked Bill Timestamp will hold the Original Message Identifier of the Sea Bill to which the Ocean Bill Of Lading Number and House Bill of Lading Number have been matched.
Note: Business rules ensure that the Master Bill fields are mutually exclusive.

Property.name: LinkingConsignmentReference
Property.description: The cleansed (removing characters based on a set of rules) version of the reference number supplied by Industry client to identify their consignment, for linking purposes between Import Declaration Cargo Line and Air Consignment.

Property.name: LinkingHouseAirWaybillId
Property.description: This attribute is used for linking the import declaration to the cargo report.  By removing characters based on a set of rules this attribute will match the House Air Waybill number on the cargo report

Property.name: LinkingHouseBillOfLadgNum
Property.description: This attribute is used for linking the import declaration to the cargo report.  By removing characters based on a set of rules this attribute will match the House Bill of Lading Number on the cargo report

Property.name: LinkingOceanBillOfLadgNum
Property.description: This attribute is used for linking the import declaration to the cargo report.  By removing characters based on a set of rules this attribute will match the ocean bill of lading on the cargo report

Property.name: MarksAndNumberDescription
Property.description: A free text field describing the package marks and numbers for all packages associated with the line of cargo and any other identifying marks and brands on the packages being imported.  Marks descriptions are usually listed on the packing list and Bill of Lading or Air Waybill.

Property.name: MasterAirWaybillId
Property.description: The number that identifies the master air waybill for the line of cargo. Where the transportation of the goods is handled directly by the airline company this is the master air waybill for the goods. Where the transportation of the goods is arranged by a cargo handler it is the master air waybill under which the cargo handler issued the house air waybill for the goods. In this case the master air waybill number is used in conjunction with the house air waybill number to uniquely identify the house air waybill.

Property.name: OceanBillOfLadingNumber
Property.description: The number that identifies the ocean bill of lading for the line of cargo. Where the transportation of the goods is handled directly by the shipping company this is the ocean bill of lading for the goods. Where the transportation of the goods is arranged by a cargo handler it is the ocean bill of lading under which the cargo handler issued the house bill of lading for the goods. In this case the ocean bill of lading number is used in conjunction with the house bill of lading number to uniquely identify the house bill of lading.

Property.name: PackageCount
Property.description: The number of packages per consignment packed in such a way that they cannot be divided without first undoing the packing.  Where goods are unpacked, enter the number of such goods covered by the consignment.

Property.name: PackingUnitCount
Property.description:
This field allows user to identify and input the number of packing units as distinct from the number of packages.  Completion of this field is not mandatory, however if the information is available it should be input, particularly for Sea Cargo.  An example of how this field can be utilised is if a bill of lading quotes 3 pallets said to contain 300 packages.  Therefore packing unit count is 3.  

This attribute is only populated for declarations where the mode of transport is sea.

Property.name: ReportedConsignmentReference
Property.description: The reference number supplied by Industry client to identify their consignment

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the line.

Property.name: VisualExmntnApplicationInd
Property.description: Indicates that a Visual Examination Application has been lodged for the consignment specified on the Declaration.

Property.name: WarehouseMarksAndNumbersDscn
Property.description: The description of the marks and numbers of the packages placed in the warehouse.

Property.name: WarehousePackageCount
Property.description: The count of packages warehoused where some (N10/20), or all (N20), packages are to be warehoused.

Property.name: XraySendRequiredIndicator
Property.description:
Describes the status of the Container XRay message.

Y       = message required and not yet sent
N       = message required and sent
blank = no message required

Property.name: CreationTimestamp
Property.description: The time at which the action was recorded.

Property.name: ReasonDescription
Property.description: A description of the reason why the action was taken.

Property.name: ReasonType
Property.description: The type or classification of the reason for taking the action. (Not applicable to all action types.)

Property.name: Type
Property.description: The type of action.

Property.name: Userid
Property.description: The user-id of the Customs officer that took the action.

Property.name: Amount
Property.description: The amount of the deferral payment.

Property.name: DeferralPeriodEndDate
Property.description: The date that is the last day of the deferral period.

Property.name: DeferralPeriodStartDate
Property.description: The date that is the first day of the deferral period.

Property.name: DueDate
Property.description: The date on which the deferral payment is due to be made.

Property.name: ImporterClientInstanceId
Property.description: The client instance id, in the client component, of the importer that deferred the liability.

Property.name: InstanceId
Property.description: The instance id of the deferral payment of one or more declarations.  This is used to interface the Financial Transaction.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: DrawbackIdentifier
Property.description: Unique customs document identifier allocated to the drawback claim.

Property.name: ConvertedGrossWeight
Property.description: The gross weight for the goods in the import declaration expressed in kilograms.  It includes any packing but not the carrier's equipment.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the current snapshot for the import declaration header derived and calculated details.

Property.name: CustomsValueFactorValue
Property.description: A factor calculated by dividing the calculated Customs Value by the Invoice total.  This is then used to calculate toe Customs Value for each line.

Property.name: EffectiveDutyDate
Property.description: The date used to determine the rates of duty applicable for the declaration. It is also used to determine the reference data applicable for validating the declaration. (With the exception of  currencies which use the valuation date.) It may be supplied but is normally calculated.  If it is not supplied it is the latest of the lodgement date and the first arrival date. However it can not be a future date. So if the first arrival date is in the future, the current date is used. (It is not possible for the lodgement date to be in the future.) This means that for an original import declaration the current date will always be used.

Property.name: TransportInsuranceFactorValue
Property.description: A factor calculated by dividing the Transport and Insurance by the calculated Customs Value.  This is then used to calculate the Transport and Insurance for each line.

Property.name: PropertyType
Property.description:
A code that records a document property that affects the processing that occurs for this import.
CODETYPE: IDPROCTYPE

Property.name: AqisInspectionLocationName
Property.description: Free Text field used to specify the AQIS location when AQIS Premises Identifier is not specified at line level.

Property.name: BrokerageReference
Property.description: A reference allocated by the broker and used by them to identify the declaration.

Property.name: ContactPhoneNumber
Property.description: Contact phone number supplied for the transaction.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the current snapshot for the import declaration header.

Property.name: DestinationPortCode
Property.description: The UNLOCODE for the Port where the goods are to be cleared from Customs control.

Property.name: EffectiveDutyDate
Property.description: The effective duty date that has been input. The effective duty date is usually calculated using the lodgement date and the first arrival date. If it is supplied it overrides the calculation of this date. However, it results in the import declaration being selected for red-line processing.

Property.name: GstDeferralIndicator
Property.description: This shows that the ABN/CAC quoted on this version of the import declaration can defer GST.  In this case the GST will not be payable to Customs but deferred and collected by the ATO at a later stage.

Property.name: ImporterAbnCcid
Property.description: The ABN or CCID for the importer as supplied within the BSF for EDI or from the UI. This is the unvalidated data.  Once the import declaration has been validated then the Importer Client Instance Id will be set to the instance that matches the valid importer.

Property.name: ImporterCacNumber
Property.description: For an importer that is a registered business, the client activity centre allocated by the ATO that is applicable to the the import declaration.

Property.name: ImporterClientInstanceId
Property.description: The instance identifier of the client who is the importer making the declaration; or on whose behalf the declaration is being made.

Property.name: ImporterReference
Property.description: A reference allocated by the importer and used by them to identify the declaration.

Property.name: InvoiceTermType
Property.description:
The type of contract terms in which the goods are sold for export. This is used in conjunction with the valuation elements to calculate the total customs value for the declaration.

Code Type value = INVTERMTYP

Property.name: LctQuoteIndicator
Property.description: This shows that the ABN/CAC quoted on this version of the import declaration can quote LCT.  In this case the importer can put off paying any LCT until the time the goods are sold.  In this case LCT will not be payable to Customs but will collected by the ATO when the goods are sold.

Property.name: N30MarksAndNumbersText
Property.description: For an ex-warehouse declaration, a free text field describing the package marks and numbers for all packages associated with the ex-warehouse declaration and any other identifying marks and brands on the packages being cleared from the warehouse.

Property.name: NilReturnIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the import declaration is a weekly settlement Nil Return. That is, a weekly settlement import declaration where no goods were delivered into home consumption during the settlement period.

Property.name: PackageCount
Property.description: For an ex-warehouse (N30) declaration, the number of packages packed in such a way that they cannot be divided without first undoing the packing.

Property.name: Section70ReturnIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the import declaration is for goods that have previously been cleared under section 70 of the Customs Act as "special clearance goods".

Property.name: SettlementPeriodEndDate
Property.description: For an ex-warehouse declaration made under the provisions of a weekly settlement permission, it is the date that is the last day of the settlement period.

Property.name: SettlementPeriodStartDate
Property.description: For an ex-warehouse declaration made under the provisions of a weekly settlement permission, it is the date that is the first day of the settlement period.

Property.name: ValuationAdviceNumber
Property.description: A valudation advice number quoted on the header of a import declaration.  An importer can apply to Customs for valuation advice and then they may quote this advice number in the future when importing goods purchased using the same valuation method.  This protects the importer from penalties.

Property.name: ValuationDate
Property.description: The date, usually the date of export of the goods, used to determine the applicable exchange rate for converting the foreign currency amounts into Australian dollars.

Property.name: WarehouseEstablishmentId
Property.description: For a warehouse declaration (N20), the identifier of the warehouse establishment that the goods are to be received into. For an ex-warehouse declaration (N30), the the identifier of the warehouse premises that the goods are to be delivered from. The warehouse must be licensed under section 79 of the Customs act to be used for warehousing goods.

Property.name: WeeklySettlementIndicator
Property.description: This indicator is only applicable to Nature 30 Declarations. A Nature 30 is for goods that are being released from a customs controlled warehouse and any duties and taxes must be paid for the goods. Some warehouses have been approved to release goods without a Nature 30 declaration and can place all the goods released during the week on one Nature 30. This indicator shows whether the goods have been released during the week.

Property.name: WetQuoteIndicator
Property.description: This shows that the ABN/CAC quoted on this version of the import declaration can quote WET.  In this case the importer can put off paying any WET until the time the goods are sold.  In this case WET will not be payable to Customs but will collected by the ATO when the goods are sold.

Property.name: AqisServicesPaymentAmount
Property.description: An amount to be paid to AQIS as part of processing the declaration.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the AQIS Services Payment Amount will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the AQIS Services Payment Amount in the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the AQIS Services Payment Amount between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: AuthoritySecurityCan
Property.description: The authority security c.. a.. number that identifies the ...  Generated using the same routine that generates a CDI. It is generated by the Outbound process when the Authority to Deal is generated. It can be used at a later stage to check against the declaration to ensure that the Authority to Deal was generated from Customs.

Property.name: BankAccountBsbNumber
Property.description: The Bank State Branch that the account for the import declaration will be paid from.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the BSB Number will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the BSB Number in the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the BSB Number between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: BankAccountName
Property.description: The Bank Account Name that the account for the import declaration will be paid from.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the Bank Account Name will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the Bank Account Name in the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the Bank Account Name between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: BankAccountNumber
Property.description: The Bank Account Number that the account for the import declaration will be paid from.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the Bank Account Number will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the Bank Account Number in the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the Bank Account Number between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: BankAccountOwnerType
Property.description: Indicates that the payment for the import declaration is coming from either the importers or brokers bank account.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the Bank Account Owner Type will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the Bank Account Owner Type within the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the Bank Account Owner Type between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: BranchIdentifier
Property.description: The identifier of the branch of the client that is responsible for the transaction message.

Property.name: ChangeDescription
Property.description: A description of the reason why the import declaration is being amended or withdrawn. It is only required for withdrawals and for post payment amendments.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the current version of the import declaration.

Property.name: DocumentOwnerClntInstanceId
Property.description: If the declaration transaction message was created by EDI this is the instance id of who submitted the message.  this is referred to as the declaration owner.  If the declaration transaction message was created interactively then the userid will show who created the transaction message.  For each user id the client component can determine an instance id which will be stored here when the transaction message is created interactively.

Property.name: DocumentOwnerType
Property.description: What type of user owns the document.  This tell us whether the Owner Client Instance Id is a broker, an importer or  Customs.

Property.name: EftPaymentApprovedInd
Property.description: Indicates that the payment for the import declaration is pre approved.  If the declaration passes validation and is not held and therefore ready to pay payment will be processed and the declaration will be paid.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed.  Once the declaration is successfully lodged the indicator will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction.  It is possible for the EFT payment approved indicator in the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the EFT payment approved indicator between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged.  This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: EftPaymentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the payment or refund is to be made by EFT.  This attribute is used to store the value while the declaration is being processed. Once the declaration is successfully lodged the indicator will be passed to the payments component to create a financial transaction. It is possible for the EFT payment indicator with the financial transaction to be updated.  This attribute is only for storing the EFT payment indicator between the time the declaration is created to being successfully lodged. This attribute is not to be used for any purpose apart from to pass to the payment component when the financial transaction is first created.

Property.name: FirstPupImportDeclarationId
Property.description: The first import declaration that was paid under protest.  The first pup declaration will have the paid under protest description that is also applicable to this declaration.

Property.name: LineLiabilityIndicator
Property.description: Assuming the transaction message is successfully processed then the outbound Import Declaration Advice message will contain some calculated amounts. If this indicator is N then no line amounts will be supplied in the outbound message otherwise some line amounts will be supplied.

Property.name: NomineeBrokerLicenceNumber
Property.description: The licence number of the individual broker responsible for the transaction.

Property.name: PaymentDueDate
Property.description: The date that the payment is due to Customs. This is defined by a Customs user when entering the Change Reason.

Property.name: PreLodgmentIndicator
Property.description: The Declaration is submitted for processing just to get a response with any errors or liabilities calculated. The Declaration is not a legal lodgement and theoretically should not be stored. In reality it is stored just for processing and will be deleted just like any normal lodgement that had errors. All processing up to but not including the actual lodgement will be performed.

Property.name: TotalLiabilityIndicator
Property.description: Assuming the transaction message is successfully processed then the outbound Import Declaration Advice message will contain some calculated amounts. If this indicator is N then only a few payable amounts will be supplied in the outbound message otherwise a lot more amounts will be supplied.

Property.name: Amount
Property.description: The monetary amount.

Property.name: AmountTypeInstanceId
Property.description: The code used to refer to the type of monetary amount.

Property.name: CurrencyCode
Property.description: The ISO currency code of the currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the line.

Property.name: Amount
Property.description: The total dollar amount of quota for the instrument for this version of the import declaration.

Property.name: InstrumentNumber
Property.description: The instrument number has different formats depending on the type.

Property.name: InstrumentType
Property.description: the type of instrument which is a code list.

Property.name: QuantityAmount
Property.description: The total quantity of quota for the instrument for this version of the import declaration.

Property.name: CheckType
Property.description: The type of check that results from the processing of the CP risk. If the CP risk does not have an associated question, the line will be selected for community protection checking. If  it does have an associated question and the high risk response is given, it will be selected for community protection checking. However, if the low risk response is given, a small percentage of lines are selected for quality control checking.   See the "community protection check type" code list".

Property.name: CmntyPrtnRiskIdentifier
Property.description:
Is the 'foreign key' to support the implied relationship is_for one Community Protection Risk.

In accordance with the CS3.0 design standard this relationship is not implemented because it crosses subject area boundaries.

Property.name: PermitNotFound
Property.description: The Permit supplied does not exist.

Property.name: PermitNotSupplied
Property.description: A Permit is required and has not been supplied.

Property.name: PermitNumber
Property.description: A number identifying a permit, certificate or some other kind of supporting document that is relevant to the assessment of the risk.

Property.name: PermitPrefixIncorrect
Property.description: The Permit Supplied is the wrong prefix for the Risk matched.

Property.name: PermitQuantityCheckNeeded
Property.description: This indicates that either the ICS has checked the quantity and had an issue or cant check the quantity due to the PIA not supplying adequate details. An officer must check the permit is valid to be used.

Property.name: PermitStatusIncorrect
Property.description: The Permit does not have a valid status to be used.

Property.name: ProfileAgencyCode
Property.description:
Customs or AQIS
Value: C or A

Property.name: ProfileBusinessIdentifier
Property.description:
The identifier of the profile that was matched by CP profile matching. This attribute will only have a non zero value when a profile that corresponds to the risk has been matched.  

For EDI the importer may supply answers to more CP profiles that are matched. In this case this field will be zero and the fields input will not be validated at all.

Property.name: ProfileRandomQualityPctg
Property.description: Describes the percentage of profile matches to be reported for quality checking.

Property.name: ProfileRandomSamplePercentage
Property.description: Describes the percentage of profile matches to be reported.

Property.name: ProfileType
Property.description:
Alert, Profile, Subsidiary or IDH.
Values: A, P, S or I

The type or area of uncertainty. (eg. origin, classification, treatment code)

Property.name: AqisCmdtyStatClassIid
Property.description: The instance id of the AQIS Commodity Statistical Class. This instance Id is used as a link to the Import Declaration AQIS Commodity.

Property.name: AqisCommodityCode
Property.description: The AQIS Commodity Code that further classifies the the Tariff Classification for the Line.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: ExceptionType
Property.description: The type of reason or exception why an AQIS commodity has not been specified for goods for the import declaration line. (Not Listed, Not Known)

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the AQIS commodity (or exemption type) for the import declaration line.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: TypeCode
Property.description: Nominated documentation type code for the line which refers to certification issued by an overseas government for food consignments.  It gives AQIS an assurance that the food will meet AQIS imported food requirements.  Not all food or countries participate in the scheme.

Property.name: AqisEntityIdentifier
Property.description: The identifier used by AQIS to identify the entity.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: Number

Property.name: Code

The code for the package type. See "package type" code list. 

Code Type value = PACKTYP

Property.name: Count
Property.description: The number of packages of the type for the line.

Property.name: AqisPremisesIdentifier
Property.description: The Premises where the good will be subject to some AQIS Processing.

Property.name: AqisProcessingTypeCode
Property.description: The code for the type of AQID Processing that the goods require.

Property.name: AqisProducerCode
Property.description: The producer code as allocated by AQIS and nominated by the importer for the declaration.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: CharacteristicCode
Property.description: A characteristic code can be attached to tariff's, instrument's etc and then that object will have extra business rules based on the characteristic code.

Property.name: SourceReference
Property.description: The Reference file item where the characteristic was sourced from. For example if this characteristic code was stored due to an Instrument used on the import declaration line then this field will contain the instrument type and instrument number. This enables future validations and calculations to know why the characteristic is being processed.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: Number
Property.description: The number that identifies the container.

Property.name: QuantityUnit
Property.description: The unit the quantity is in.  Eg KG for kilograms, NO for number.

Property.name: QuantityValue
Property.description: The value that is the quantity of goods.

Property.name: UnitCustomsValueAmount
Property.description: The customs value of one unit of the given unit of quantity.  This is used to validate the goods are in a specified value range.

Property.name: UnitTAndIAmount
Property.description: The cost of the transport insurance for one unit of the given unit of quantity. This information may be used by the broker to calculate the transport and insurance amount that must be input on the ex-warehouse declaration, when some of the goods for the line are taken out of the warehouse.

Property.name: AddDutyCalcIdentifier
Property.description:
When a Tariff or Treatment code that has been used to calculate the Actual Customs Duty has more than one calculation this shows which additional calculation was used to calculate the duty.  

If the Duty Treatment Code is spaces and the Add Duty Calc Identifier is zero then the duty was calculated using the rate in the Tariff Rate Period Snpsht Entity.

If the Duty Treatment Code is spaces and the Add Duty Calc Identifier is not zero then the duty was calculated using the rate in the Tariff Rate Period Add Duty Calc Entity where the identifier matches this attibute.

If the Duty Treatment Code is not spaces and the Add Duty Calc Identifier is zero then the duty was calculated using the rate in the Treatment Rate Period Snpsht Entity.

If the Duty Treatment Code is not spaces and the Add Duty Calc Identifier is not zero then the duty was calculated using the rate in the Treatment RatePeriod Add Duty Calc Entity where the identifier matches this attibute.

Property.name: ConcessnlRatePeriodSnpshtIid
Property.description: The instance id of the version of the Tariff Rate Period Snapshot that details the General Rate.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the current snapshot for the import declaration line derived and calculated details.

Property.name: DutySelectionType
Property.description: A code that shows where the duty rates have been selected from.  Depending on what tariff classifications and treatment codes have been supplied the duty rates for actual duty, standard duty and general duty may be calculated from either the duty rates for one of the tariff classifications or treatment codes.

Property.name: DutyTariffClassNumber
Property.description: The tariff classification that was used to calculate duty

Property.name: DutyTreatmentCode
Property.description: The treatment code that was used to calculated duty

Property.name: GeneralTariffRtePdSnpshtIid
Property.description: The instance id of the version of the Tariff Rate Period Snapshot that details the General Rate.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the line.

Property.name: StatisticalQuantityUnit
Property.description: The Quantity Unit that is required by a Tariff Statistical Classification. The report that is generated to send to the Australian Bureau of Statistics includes the one quantity that the ABS wants to use for reporting purposes. This is the Quantity Unit the ABS requires for this Import Declaration Line. This allows the report to be produced without having to re read reference files to determine which quantity unit the ABS requires.

Property.name: StndardTariffRtePdShpshtIid
Property.description: The instance id of the version of the Tariff Rate Period Snapshot that details the General Rate.

Property.name: TariffQuotaQuantityUnit
Property.description: The Quantity Unit that a Tariff Quota instrument quoted on the declaration is measured in.  For example an instrument might have been issued to an importer to allow a reduce duty rate to be used for cheese up to 100KG.  This attibute is used to calculate the amount used by the import declaration without having to re read reference files to determine which quantity unit the Tariff Quota is measured in.

Property.name: TreatmentRatePeriodShpshtIid
Property.description: The instance id of the version of the Tariff Rate Period Snapshot that details the General Rate.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: Number
Property.description: The number that identifies the Excess Local Area Content (ELAC) authority.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the current snapshot for the import declaration line.

Property.name: DumpingExchangeRateAmount
Property.description: Used in conjunction with Dumping Export Country Code to specify a rate of exchange for currency conversion.  It replaces the system rate of exchange.

Property.name: DumpingExemptionType
Property.description:
Where the tariff/statistical classification indicates that dumping may be applicable, but it is not applicable in this case, the dumping exemption type is used to specify the reason these particular goods are not subject to dumping.

Code Type value = DUMPEXETYP

Property.name: DumpingExportCountryCode
Property.description: Where dumping is applicable to the tariff / statistical classifcation for the goods and the country from which the goods were exported differs from the country of origin this is the 2 character ISO country code for the country from which the goods were exported.

Property.name: DumpingReasmtUpdatedUserId
Property.description: The user responsible for changing the dumping reassessment indicator.

Property.name: DumpingReassessmentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates whether a Declaration Line has been manually identified for reassessment due to the goods content being deemed as dumped onto the Australian market.

Property.name: DumpingSpecificationNumber
Property.description: Where dumping is applicable to the goods for the line this is the number of applicable dumping specification.

Property.name: FirmOrderDate
Property.description: Used to enter goods concessionally after a Tariff Concession or other instrument has been revoked but "in transit" provisions apply.  To use this field the goods must be made-to-order capital equipment that is classified within Tariff Chapters 84-90.  The Firm Order Date must be fall between the date the instrument came into force and the date it was revoked.

Property.name: GoodsDescription
Property.description: Plain language description of the nature of the goods sufficient to identify them at the level required for banking, Customs, Statistical or transport purposes. It should be expressed in precise terms to allow the classification of goods.

Property.name: GstExemptionCode
Property.description:
The type of GST exemption applicable to the goods.

Code Type value = GSTX

Property.name: ImportCreditNumber
Property.description: A number identifying an Import Credit Scheme account.  An importer can quote this number when they wish to offset duty amounts that would normally be payable on an importation.  The ICN relates to a balance in A$ which is the total amount of credits available for offset.

Property.name: InstrumentSecurityCode
Property.description: Some instruments have a security code.  This restricts usage to importers who are not only setup to be allowed to use the instrument but also know the security code.

Property.name: InvoiceSpiritStrengthPercentg
Property.description: For alcohol products, it is the alcohol content as a percentage of the total volume of product being entered.

Property.name: LctExemptionCode
Property.description: The type of luxury car tax (LCT) exemption applicable to the goods. (See LCT exemption codes reference file.)

Property.name: LctPayableIndicator
Property.description: An indicator to show the importer requires LCT to be calculated and they will pay the amount that the system calculates.  The calculation is based on one car so the quantity supplied must be one.

Property.name: LctQuoteIndicator
Property.description: Indicates the importer is quoting the Luxury Car Tax (LCT) liability for the line.  This means that the payment of LCT is deferred until the last retail sale and does not have to be paid on the declaration.  This arrangement is intended for high volume luxury car importers.  The importer must be approved by the Australian Tax Office to be allowed to quote LCT.

Property.name: LineActionCode
Property.description: Shows whether the line has been inserted, changed or deleted.

Property.name: LocalContentPercentage
Property.description: For preference purposes identifies the percentage of local content of the goods in relation to the claim for preference. It is used in determining which duty rate is applicable.

Property.name: ManualLineProcessingInd
Property.description: Shows that the duty for the line has been manually calculated and supplied

Property.name: MultipleClearanceCode
Property.description: A Customs allocated number used in place of original N.20 Warehousing Declaration numbers.  It is used on N.30 ex-Warehousing Declarations when product is unable to be linked to the original N.20 Declaration, eg for warehousing entries older than 5 years, weekly settlement consolidated references and blended product.

Property.name: NatureType
Property.description:
The nature type of import declaration line. Home consumption, warehousing or ex-warehousing. 

Code Type value = LINENATTYP

Property.name: OtherDutyFactorValue
Property.description: An additional factor used with the system-held duty rate to calculate duty.

Property.name: PaidUnderProtestIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the line has been nominated by the broker as being paid under protest.

Property.name: PreferenceOriginCountryCode
Property.description: The 2 character ISO country code for the country that is the origin of the goods for the purposes of the rules of preference, where this is different from the country of origin.

Property.name: PreferenceRuleType
Property.description: Where supplied, the rule for the preference scheme applicable to the goods for the line allowing preference to be claimed for the goods.

Property.name: PreferenceSchemeType
Property.description: Where supplied the preference scheme under which a preferential rate of duty is being claimed.

Property.name: RefundReasonCode
Property.description: This is the code used on a declaration where a refund is to be paid. It indicates the reason why a refund is payable and identifies the regulation being used to claim the refund as defined in Reg 126 of the Customs Regulations.

Property.name: RelatedTransactionIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that there is a relationship between the supplier of the goods and the importer.

Property.name: SecondTariffClassNumber
Property.description:
The tariff classification that duty calculation will be based on when this is different to the tariff classification of the goods. For example a crane is being imported in parts and this import declaration is for the wheels.  The Tariff Classification field will be for the wheels, but as the duty will be based on the whole crane the Second Tariff Classification field will be for the crane.

Note: When the Second Tariff Classification is supplied all rules for duty calculation and concessions will be based on this tariff item and the Tariff Classification field is only for information.

Property.name: SecondTreatmentCode
Property.description: In some cases more than one concessional item may be applicable to the goods so a second treatment code is required. For example a temporary importation where another concessional item is applicable to the goods reducing the amount of security required.

Property.name: SecurityCalculateIndicator
Property.description: This indicator signifies that the Security Amount must be calculated and reported back to the partly responsible for the Import Declaration.

Property.name: SecurityIdentifier
Property.description: A Customs-allocated security number that must be quoted when the goods being entered are subject to compliance with either end-use conditions, dumping/countervailing provisional measures or temporary importations.

Property.name: SecurityInstanceId
Property.description: The unique instance id of a Security.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the line.

Property.name: StatClassPeriodSnpshtIid
Property.description: The unique instance id of a Statistical Classification Period Snapshot.

Property.name: StatisticalClassCode
Property.description: The code for the statistical classification for the tariff classification applicable to the goods for the line.

Property.name: SupplierClientInstanceId
Property.description: The client instance id that of the Supplier of the goods.  Suppliers must be registered in the client registration system.

Property.name: SupplierIdentifier
Property.description: The identifier for the supplier as supplied within the BSF for EDI or from the UI.  This is the unvalidated data.  Once the import declaration has been validated then the Supplier Client Instance Id will be set to the instance that matches the valid supplier.

Property.name: SupplierTin
Property.description: The (Trusted) Trader Identification Number of the Supplier

Property.name: TariffAdviceNumber
Property.description: A number allocated by Customs that is used to identify the advice.

Property.name: TariffClassificationNumber
Property.description: The number of the tariff classification applicable to the goods for the line.

Property.name: TariffClassificationRateNum
Property.description: The rate number used to allow a tariff classification to have different rates of duty for different reasons. Tariff Rates Numbers are specified in the Tariff. Generally there is only one value, RNO=01 but other tariff rate numbers can be used when required.

Property.name: TreatmentCode
Property.description: Where supplied it is the code that identifies the concessional item in Schedule 4 or Supplementary Provisions that goods are entered under.

Property.name: TreatmentCodeRateNumber
Property.description: Used to nominate a specific Rate for the Treatment Code. Treatment Codes may have more than one Rate for different reasons. Generally there is only one value, (e.g.; RNO = 01) however other Treatment Code Rate Numbers can be used when required. Treatment Code Rate Numbers are specified in Schedule 4 of the Tariff. Additionally, the Treatment Code Rate Number attribute will be used to allow input of a Quota Item Number where a Tariff Quota concession is being claimed. Tariff Quotas will be nominated on a Declaration by using the appropriate Treatment Code and Instrument (TFQ) combination. The Quota Item Number is only required to be supplied where more than one Quota Rate exists

Property.name: ValuationAdviceNumber
Property.description: A number allocated by Customs that is used to identify the advice.

Property.name: ValuationBasisType
Property.description: The type of valuation basis used to derive the customs value.  Relates to the particular Valuation method utilised to value goods for the Customs transaction.

Property.name: VendorIdentifier
Property.description: The Vendor Identifier may contain either a Vendor Registration Number (VRN) or an Australian Business Number (ABN). The VRN is the number registered to an overseas Vendor who may have an online shop or supply goods to an Australian consumer.  If a Vendor has a registered business in Australia, the Vendors can apply for and use an ABN. These vendors collect GST at the point of sale, and remit it to the ATO directly.

Property.name: WarehouseDecLineNumber
Property.description: On a N.30 (ex-warehouse) Import Declaration, it is the Line Number of the Line for the goods on the the N.20 (warehouse) Import Declaration on which the goods were originally entered.

Property.name: WarehouseDeclarationId
Property.description: On a N.30 (ex-warehouse) Import Declaration, it is the Customs Document Identifier of the N.20 (warehouse) Import Declaration on which the goods were originally entered.

Property.name: WetExemptionCode
Property.description:
The type of wine equalisation tax (WET) exemption applicable to the goods. 

Code Type value = WETX

Property.name: WetQuoteIndicator
Property.description: Indicates the importer is quoting the wine equalisation tax (WET) liability for the line. This means that the payment of WET is deferred until the last retail sale and does not have to be paid on the declaration. This arrangement is intended for high volume wine importers. The importer must be approved by the Australian Taxation Office to be allowed to quote WET.

Property.name: ApplicabilityType
Property.description:
An instrument may be called for by a tariff classification or a treatment code. A line allows for two tariff classifications and two treatment codes to be input. The applicability type indicates which of these the instrument relates to. See the "Instrument Applicability Type" code list. 

Code Type value = IDLNEINAPP

Property.name: ApplicabilityTypeSequence
Property.description: The sequence number of the instrument for the applicability type. For example, if the treatment code called for a Bylaw and the Bylaw called for a TCO; the Bylaw and the TCO would both have the applicability "TRT" indicating that they relate to the treatment code. However the applicability type sequence would be "1" for the Bylaw and "2" for the TCO.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: Number
Property.description: The number that identifies the instrument.

Property.name: Type
Property.description:
The code for the type of instrument. eg. Determination, Tariff Concession, By-Law. See the "Instrument Type" code list. 

Code Type value = INSTRMTTYP

Property.name: MessageAdviceIdentifier
Property.description: The number of the message.

Property.name: CountryCode
Property.description: The 2 character ISO country code for the country that is the country of origin for all or for some portion of component of the goods.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence or order in which the origin countries were supplied. Where there is more than one origin given, the first origin is taken to be the origin of the greatest proportion of the goods.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: PackageCount
Property.description: The number of packages of the type,for the line.

Property.name: Type
Property.description:
The code for the type of package. See the "Package Type" code list. 

Code Type value = PACKTYP

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: QuantityUnit
Property.description: The unit of quantity in which the quantity value is expressed.

Property.name: QuantityValue
Property.description: The quantity of goods.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence or order in which the quantities were supplied.

Property.name: WarehouseQuantityUnitInd
Property.description: On a warehouse entry (ie Nature 20) indicates that this is the unit of quantity that the importer of the goods expects to use later to clear the goods. If the importer expects to sell the goods based on different units of quantity depending on the buyer then more than one unit of quantity can have this indicator set.

Property.name: DeletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates if the record has been deleted.

Property.name: VehicleIdentificationNumber
Property.description: The unique identification number allocated by the vehicle manufacturer to the motor vehicle.

Property.name: AnswerType
Property.description: Where the lodgement declaration is a question, this is the answer to the question. The answer must be yes (Y) or no (N).

Property.name: Identifier
Property.description: The unique identifier allocated to the lodgement question or declaration or the Community Protection Risk Identifier

Property.name: QuestionIndicator
Property.description: Shows whether this was supplied on the import declaration as a question or a declaration. "Y" shows this a question otherwise it was supplied as a declaration.

Property.name: ReferralReasonDescription
Property.description: For the "quarantine concerns" or the "community protection concerns" question for a self assessed clearance, where the question is answered yes ("Y") this is a description of the reason why it has been nominated as a concern.

Property.name: Number
Property.description: The number allocated by the post office that is used to identify the parcel post card.

Property.name: CreateTimestamp
Property.description: The current timestamp at the time the record was created.

Property.name: CreateUserId
Property.description: The user ID of the user who made the request.

Property.name: CustomsInternalEmailIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the email was sent to a customs internal email address.

Property.name: EmailAddress
Property.description: The email address on an email request

Property.name: NetworkPrinterId
Property.description: The ID of the network printer on a print request

Property.name: PrintRequestIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the request was a print request.

Property.name: SystemGeneratedRequestInd
Property.description: Indicates that the request was generated by the system during FID processing.

Property.name: Type
Property.description: The code allocated by AQIS for the concern.  For example LCLP - LCL packing ,STRW - straw, BVOL - broker volunteered, RURL - rural unpack.

Property.name: Number
Property.description: The number allocated by AQIS and used to identify the AQIS permit.

Property.name: AqisPremisesIdentifier
Property.description: The Premises where the good will be subject to some AQIS Processing.

Property.name: AqisProcessingType
Property.description: The type of processing that the goods require.

Property.name: Sequence
Property.description: The sequence in which the AQIS processing details were supplied.

Property.name: AqisPackagingInformationInd
Property.description: Indicates that the cargo line(s) contain any AQIS packaging Concerns.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the snapshot is the current snapshot for the RCR cargo.

Property.name: UniqueConsignmentRefNumber
Property.description: International Number for Identifying Cargo.

Property.name: Amount
Property.description: The amount for the revenue sub-heading.

Property.name: DeferredLiabilityIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the liability amount applicable to the revenue sub heading has been deferred.

Property.name: RevenueSubHeadCode
Property.description: FMIS Revenue Sub-Head issues by Financial Services Branch.

Property.name: GoodsDescription
Property.description: The description of the goods.  This is used by a SAC as the goods description on a full dec will always be entered at line level.

Property.name: ImporterName
Property.description: A SAC may be supplied by an importer who is not registered.  For a SAC where the importer is registered then the importer client instance id in the import decl hdr input snpsht will hold the instance id of the importer.  Otherwise the importers name must be supplied and will be stored here.

Property.name: OriginCountryCode
Property.description: The country code from which the goods have been imported.

Property.name: SupplierClientInstanceId
Property.description: A SAC may only specify a supplier at header level.  A Full Dec can have a different supplier for each line.  For a SAC where the supplier is registered this is the supplier identifier.  If the Supplier is not registered then the name must be supplied and will be stored in the supplier name attribute.

Property.name: SupplierIdentifier
Property.description: The identifier for the supplier as supplied within the BSF for EDI or from the UI.  This is the unvalidated data.  Once the import declaration has been validated then the Supplier Client Instance Id will be set to the instance that matches the valid supplier.

Property.name: SupplierName
Property.description: A SAC may only specify a supplier at header level.  A Full Dec can have a different supplier for each line.  For a SAC where the supplier is not registered this is the supplier name.

Property.name: SupplierTin
Property.description: The (Trusted) Trader Identification Number of the Supplier

Property.name: VendorIdentifier
Property.description: The Vendor Identifier may contain either a Vendor Registration Number (VRN) or an Australian Business Number (ABN). The VRN is the number registered to an overseas Vendor who may have an online shop or supply goods to an Australian consumer.  If a Vendor has a registered business in Australia, the Vendors can apply for and use an ABN. These vendors collect GST at the point of sale, and remit it to the ATO directly.

Property.name: Amount
Property.description: The amount of security concession used for the seciruty identifier for this version of the declaration.

Property.name: SecurityIdentifier
Property.description: The Customs Document Identifier of the Security.

Property.name: CanDeferLiabilityIndicator
Property.description: Indicates whether this instance of the Import Declaration is eligible to defer payment of liability amount(s).

Property.name: CreateUserid
Property.description: When a transaction message is created interactively this is the user id of who created the message.  If Customs interactively amends a declaration (for example to create a demand post) this will be the userid of the Customs officer who performed the amendment.

Property.name: CurrentIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that this is the transaction message that resulted in the current version of the import declaration. This will not always be the most recent transaction message. For example a rejected refund can result in the current version reverting to the last "finalised" version.

Property.name: DeferralIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the liability arising from the version of the import declaration is to be deferred.

Property.name: DemandIndicator
Property.description: Indicates that the amendment is a demand. That is it is an amendment to the import declaration that is made by Customs because the original declaration was in error resulting in an under-payment.

Property.name: FinalisedDate
Property.description: The date on which the liability arising from the transaction message was finalised. (i.e Paid, Refund Paid, Deferred)

Property.name: InstanceId
Property.description: The instance id of the version of the declaration.  This is used to interface to other sections within the ICS.  Payents hold this instance id so it knows what the payment is for.  Also the notes component is used to store PUP and AMBER statements and this instance id is used to show who owns the note..

Property.name: LodgedDate
Property.description: The date on which the message was successfully validated by Import Declaration processing.

Property.name: LodgedTime
Property.description: The time of the day on which the message was successfully validated by Import Declaration processing.

Property.name: MessageIdentifier
Property.description: The identifier of the message.

Property.name: SaveCount
Property.description: Incremented when changes are saved to a version of the Declaration. Used to prevent concurrent update by multiple transactions.

Property.name: StatusType
Property.description:
The latest status of processing for the version of the import declaration, eg, Incomplete, Complete, Rejected, Held, Paid, etc.

Code Type value = IDTMS

Property.name: TransactionType
Property.description: The type of message. (original, change or withdraw)  See "transaction type" code list.

Property.name: VersionSequence
Property.description: The system version number that the transaction has created for the Declaration.

Property.name: Type
Property.description:
The Indicator that the value is for. See Import Declaration Indicator type code list. 

Code Type value = IDINDTYP

Property.name: Value
Property.description:
The value of the indicator.
Valid values: Y, N

Property.name: CreationTimestamp
Property.description: The time that the Import Declaration Transaction Message changed to this status.

Property.name: Type
Property.description:
The status of processing for the version of the import declaration, eg, Incomplete, Complete, Rejected, Held, Paid, etc.
Code Type value = IDTMS

Property.name: ChildrenCount
Property.description: The number of Children under 18 accompanying the Importer and covered by the UPE.

Property.name: ImporterBirthDate
Property.description: The Importers Date of Birth.

Property.name: ImporterPassportCountryCode
Property.description:
The country that issued the Importers Passport.  A ICAO Country Code
CODE TYPE: ICAO

Property.name: ImporterPassportNumber
Property.description: The Passport Number for the Importer of the Goods.

Property.name: ImporterSexCode
Property.description:
Sex of the Importer.  Can have values, Male (M) Female (F), Unknown (U) or Unspecified (X).
Code Type Value = SEX_TYPE

Property.name: SpouseName
Property.description: The Name of a Spouse accompanying the Importer.

Property.name: SpousePassportCountryCode
Property.description:
The country that issued the accompanying Spouses Passport.  A ICAO Country Code
CODE TYPE: ICAO

Property.name: SpousePassportNumber
Property.description: The Passport Number for the accompanying Spouse.

Property.name: ArrivalDate
Property.description: The latest date the ship or aircraft carrying the cargo arrived or is expected to arrive at the port where the cargo is to be unloaded, sourced from IMPORT_DECL_CARGO_HDR_SNPSHT. For parcels post cargo it is the date that the parcels post card was issued.

Property.name: BrokerageReference
Property.description: The latest reference allocated by the broker and used by them to identify the declaration, sourced from IMPORT_DECL_HDR_INPUT_SNPSHT.

Property.name: CompletedIndicator
Property.description: Indicates whether a 'completed' version exists for this declaration i.e. one with a status other than INCOMPLETE, SUBMITTED or PROCESSING

Property.name: CustomsDocumentIdentifier
Property.description: The Import Declaration processing allocated Customs Document Identifier. This Identifier will be passed back to the message owner for use as a Senders Reference.

Property.description:
A code that indicates whether the cargo report is for sea cargo or air cargo.

Code Type value = TRNSPRTMDE
Values:
A = Consigned Air cargo.
S = Consigned Sea cargo.

Property.name: CarrierClientId
Property.description: The identifier of the carrier within the client component. This is an identifier assigned by Customs to carriers of export goods. Only required from Marine CTOs.

Property.name: ContingencyCan
Property.description: Manually generated document identifier to authorise the export of goods. Contingency Customs Document Identifier (Contingency Customs Authority Number) is generated by Customs officers.

Property.name: DestinationCountryCode
Property.description:
The ISO code of the final country of destination of the goods. This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Code Type value = COUNTRY

Property.name: GoodsDescription
Property.description:
Free text description of the goods.
This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: GoodsOwnerClientId
Property.description:
The identifier of the goods owner within the client component. 
This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: GoodsOwnerName
Property.description:
The Goods Owners name in free text. 
This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: LineActionType
Property.description:
A record of the action that was performed to create this line version.

Code Type value = LNACTIONCD
Values:
I = Insert. This is the original version of the line.
A = Amend. This version is an amendment of a prior version.
D = Delete. This line version is a logical delete of the line.

Property.name: LineNumber
Property.description: A number to uniquely identify and sequence the line within the one header.

Property.name: OffloadIndicator
Property.description:
An indicator indicating whether the goods referred to by the CTO identifier and Customs Authority Number have been received into the CTO due to an offload from a vessel or aircraft.
Values:
Y = Due to an offload.
N = Not due to an offload (This is the default).

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: ProposedDepartureDate
Property.description:
The intended date of departure of the vessel in local time.

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: RemovedIndicator
Property.description:
Indicates whether this combination of CAN, Cargo ID , Cargo Id Type and CTO already exits on a CTO removal for the same CTO.
Y = one or more removals exist.
N = no removal exists (This is the default value).

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: VesselRegistrationNumber

Property.name: VoyageNumber
Property.description: The carrier voyage number for this specific departure.

Property.name: DocumentVersionNumber
Property.description: The document version that the client's system has assigned to the message. This is also known as Sender's Reference Version Number.

'Y' = the entire transaction details have been received.
'N' = only part of the message/transaction has been received. This version of the notice is to be excluded from all ICS business processing. This exclusion also applies where initial lodgements are incomplete.

Property.name: MessageIdentifier
Property.description:
Identifier of the ICS Message, which contained the 
information used to create or update this notice instance.

For on-line actions, this id will be obtained by using an operation in the message component return a message id.    

Provides ordering in a chronological sequence for messages/actions against the one document.

Property.name: MessageReceivedDate
Property.description: The date the message is considered to be received by Customs. For EDI messages this is the date the message was received at the CCF. For on-line the date will be the create date.

Property.name: MessageReceivedTime

Property.name: TransactionType
Property.description:
A code that indicates the function of the message.

Code Type value = TRAN MSG
Allowed values:
O = Original
R = Full Replacement
C = Change.  Partial Replacement. The full header and the lines being amended.
W = Withdrawal of the entire document.

Property.name: AmountRangeHighValue
Property.description: The value that is compared to the Attribute on the Declaration/Report referred to by the Attribute Type.  This is only used when the Attribute on the Declaration/Report is an amount.  This is the amount that is the high value of the amount range. If this is null then all amounts that are greater than or equal to the "amount range low value" are included.

Property.name: AmountRangeLowValue
Property.description: The value that is compared to the Attribute on the Declaration/Report referred to by the Attribute Type.  This is only used when the Attribute on the Declaration/Report is an amount.  This is the amount that is the low value of the amount range. (The range is inclusive.)

Property.name: AttributeCd
Property.description:
A code for the Attribute on the Declaration/Report that is used for the condition.

Code Type value = CHRCRITCND

Property.name: CharacteristicCodeValue
Property.description: The value that is compared to the Characteristic codes that apply to the Tariff Statistical Classification quoted on an import declaration line.  When processing a condition that has a Characteristic Code Value each line of the import declaration is checked to see if the line has a Tariff Statistical Classification that has this Characteristic Code attached to it.  If so then this line will be included for the charge.  This assumes that all other condtions have already been met.

Property.name: CodeValue
Property.description: The value that is compared to the Attribute on the Declaration/Report referred to by the Attribute Type.  This is only used when the Attribute on the Declaration/Report is a code and has a code list.

Property.description: For unit charges where a maximum amount is specified, this is the number of units after which the maximum amount is applicable rather than the unit charge amount.

For unit charges it is the type of unit that is used to calculate the charge. For example if the unit type is "FCL container" the charge would be calculated by multiplying the number of FCL containers on the declaration by the charge amount.

The following is a table showing the 'business source types' and their corresponding related 'entity types':

Business Source Type - RELATED ENTITY TYPE
----------------------------------------------------------------
AQIS Service Charge - IMPORT DECLARATION
Import Declaration - IMPORT DECL TRANSACTION MESSAGE
Import Declaration Deferral Payment - IMPORT DECLARATION DEFERRAL PAYMENT
Import Periodic Declaration - IMPORT PDECL TRANSACTION MESSAGE
Manual Payment - MANUAL PAYMENT
Security - SECURITY
Drawback Claim - DRAWBACK CLAIM
Carnet - CARNET IMPORT

Property.name: CustomerReferenceNumber
Property.description:
The Customer Reference Number for the Financial Transaction Consolidation. This is the number that is used for payments using the BPAY method of payment. It is only applicable to non-EFT payments. That is where the EFT indicator = "N".
 
The format of the number is 7nnnnnnnnnC.
 
The leftmost (prefix) digit will always be "7". This number is allocated by Customs Finance Branch for ICS payments.
 
The next 9 digits (n) are a sequence number. This will be unique for all non-EFT Financial Transaction Consolidation instances.
 
The righmost digit "C" is a check digit calculated using a modulus 10 algorithm.
 
The reason that is required is that in some circumstances the Customer Reference Number must be allocated prior the creation of the FINANCIAL TRANSACTION CONSOLIDATION. In these cases there is a one to one relationship between the FINANCIAL TRANSACTION and the FINANCIAL TRANSACTION CONSOLIDATION so the Customer Reference Number is allocated when the FINANCIAL TRANSACTION is created and then reused on the FINANCIAL TRANSACTION CONSOLIDATION.

Property.name: GoodsOwnerName
Property.description:
The Goods Owners name in free text. 
This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: LineActionType
Property.description:
A record of the action that was performed to create this line version.

Code Type value = LNACTIONCD
Values:
I = Insert. This is the original version of the line.
A = Amend. This version is an amendment of a prior version.
D = Delete. This line version is a logical delete of the line.

Property.name: LineNumber
Property.description: A number to uniquely identify and sequence the line within the one header.

Property.name: OffloadIndicator
Property.description:
An indicator indicating whether the goods referred to by the CTO identifier and Customs Authority Number have been received into the CTO due to an offload from a vessel or aircraft.
Values:
Y = Due to an offload.
N = Not due to an offload (This is the default).

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: ProposedDepartureDate
Property.description:
The intended date of departure of the vessel in local time.

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: RemovedIndicator
Property.description:
Indicates whether this combination of CAN, Cargo ID , Cargo Id Type and CTO already exits on a CTO removal for the same CTO.
Y = one or more removals exist.
N = no removal exists (This is the default value).

This attribute only applies to CTO Receival Notice lines.

Property.name: VesselRegistrationNumber
Property.description: The number used to identify the vessel carrying the goods. This will usually be the Lloyds Registration Number, but may be a vessel identifier created by Customs. Also known as 'Vessel Id'.

Property.name: VoyageNumber
Property.description: The carrier voyage number for this specific departure.

Property.name: DocumentVersionNumber
Property.description: The document version that the client's system has assigned to the message. This is also known as Sender's Reference Version Number.

Property.name: MessageCompleteIndicator
Property.description:
Indicates whether the full transaction or message details have been recorded and subsequently processed. The indicator is required to support transactions/messages that are received and recorded in parts.
Values:
'Y' = the entire transaction details have been received.
'N' = only part of the message/transaction has been received. This version of the notice is to be excluded from all ICS business processing. This exclusion also applies where initial lodgements are incomplete.

Property.name: MessageIdentifier
Property.description:
Identifier of the ICS Message, which contained the 
information used to create or update this notice instance.

For on-line actions, this id will be obtained by using an operation in the message component return a message id.    

Provides ordering in a chronological sequence for messages/actions against the one document.

Property.name: MessageReceivedDate
Property.description: The date the message is considered to be received by Customs. For EDI messages this is the date the message was received at the CCF. For on-line the date will be the create date.

Property.name: MessageReceivedTime
Property.description: The time the message is considered to be received by Customs.

Property.name: TransactionType
Property.description:
A code that indicates the function of the message.

Code Type value = TRAN MSG
Allowed values:
O = Original
R = Full Replacement
C = Change.  Partial Replacement. The full header and the lines being amended.
W = Withdrawal of the entire document.

Property.name: Userid
Property.description:
The identifier of the user that initiates the transaction.

This field will be populated if the change is initiated from an on-line transaction otherwise it will be blank.

Property.name: VersionSequence
Property.description: The system version number that the transaction/message has created for the notice.

Property.name: Code
Property.description:
The code for the assigned movement status. 

Code Type value = MVMNT STS
Values for CTO Receival Notices:
LOAD = Load
DNL = Do not load
HFC = Hold for Customs

Property.name: ConditionCode
Property.description:
Provides additional information to describe the condition that resulted in the associated movement status code.

Code Type value = MVMNT COND

Property.name: CreateTimestamp
Property.description: The date and time when a Movement Status is set
